timeline.bodyText:
This is not OK:

you should target "set"+capitalize(field.name) rather than go directly via the Hibernate method.
this won't work for generics:

@Entity
public class MyEntity extends EntitySupertype<String> {}
@MappedSuperclass
public class EntitySupertype<IdType> extends PanacheEntityBase{
 @Id
 public IdType id;
}
Here, field.type() is going to return IdType even though in your case it's really String. Note that this issue may also affect your use of the id field without setter and the generic entity setter. A few tests will tell you if they're affected.

